<br>
1. Select the shape tool and set it to oval, make sure it does just a path and not a fill or anything. then take the pen tool and draw the tail so it overlaps the oval, then select the path component selection tool(which is right above the pen tool and is the black arrow, not the white) and select both paths.<br>
in the options at the top select the one on the left, whioch is add to the shape selection or something then hit combine. now select the pen tool again and right click on the path and go to fill, then right click again and go to stroke, stroke it with some tool(note: you have to go to the tool and select the size you want to stroke it with)<br>
<br>
2.draw the tail with the pen tool, hit ctr+enter to turn it into a selection. then get the circle marquee tool, hold down shift and make a circle selection so it overlaps the tail, the right click and go to fill, then stroke <p>---------------------------<br><font size=-2><a href="http://www.fhl-frisco.com/nate/index.html" target="_blank">The Art of Nathan Faubion</a><br><a href="http://pub57.ezboard.com/bchristianotaku">Association of Christian Otaku</a><br><a href="http://www.outcaststudios.com">Outcast Studios</a><br>Yvan eht <a href="http://pub90.ezboard.com/bkeepingthisfolderontop">kutoffed</a><br><a href="http://www.junkmunkies.com" underline="no">J U N K M U N K I E S</a></font><font style="display: none;"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wsl101>wsl101</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0> at: 11/26/02 11:45:22 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=comorbid>comorbid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/28/02 7:14:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4589.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.livejournal.com/userpic/953350 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Photoshop 6(?) and Word Balloons</span><hr size=1> Actually - and I know this probably looks like a lot of work, but it's mostly just descriptions of what stuff looks like - going off the basis of option 1 given by wsl101:<br>
<br>
rather than just overlapping the tail with the pen tool, use the &quot;Add Anchor Point&quot; tool, which is nested under the Pen tool (click and hold the icon to open the nested selections, it's basically the pen icon with a + on it) and add 3 points where you want the tail to be (relatively close together) to the work path created with the ellipse tool.<br>
<br>
Next, select the &quot;Convert Point&quot; tool (just for the sake of having it selected already). and hold the Ctrl (Command on a Mac) key and drag out the middle point from the 3 you just added.<br>
<br>
Let go of the Ctrl/Command key and click the point you just moved (just click it, don't do anything else), And that turns it into a corner point.<br>
<br>
Now, holding the Ctrl/Command key again, click either one of the other 2 points you added. There should be 2 lines coming off of the point in opposite directions. These are the curve handles. Let go of the Ctrl/Command key and drag the end of the handle that's pointing toward wwhere that center point used to be until you have the type of &quot;Speech Bubble Tail&quot; curve you're looking for. Do this for both of the 2 outer points you added.<br>
<br>
It might take a few tries to get that right, but it works ok.<br>
<br>
Fill that selection with white, then apply the Stroke layer style to that layer (you can preview how thick the outline wil be and you can have it sit outside, inside, or on the center of the edge of the speech bubble). If you're wondering, the Layer Style button is the black circle with the fancy &quot;f&quot; at the bottom left corner of the Layers palette.<br>
<br>
IMHO, for stuff like this, it's probably better to use Illustrator, but then there's that whole &quot;learning another program&quot; thing if you've never used it before. It really is a program worth learning, though.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=4589.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showNextMessage?topicID=4589.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4589.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.emailToFriend?topicID=4589.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.threadControl?topicID=4589.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4589.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4589.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub25.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="polykarbonbbsfrm18">PK-BBS Rules and Regulations!<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm27">Board F.A.Q.s<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm3">News and Updates<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm2">Photoshop and Art questions<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm4">General Manga/Anime Discussion<option value="polyk